@node not16 "AMIGA COMMUNITY LIAISON GROUP SPONSORS MAILING LIST"

@{FG Shine}AMIGA COMMUNITY LIAISON GROUP SPONSORS MAILING LIST@{FG Text}

@{FG Fill}DATE: 1998/05/13@{FG Text}

@{B}The Amiga Community Liaison Group@{UB}

The  @{B}Amiga  Community Liaison Group@{UB} (@{B}ACLG@{UB}) is a group being formed by members of
the @{B}ICOA@{UB}, @{B}Team Amiga@{UB}, and the @{B}Jay Miner Society@{UB}, among others, to help them keep
in touch with each other and coordinate their activities where this makes sense.
Our  intention is to include representatives from @{B}Amiga@{UB} organisations all around
the world in this.

The  first  two  subjects  considered  by  the  @{B}ACLG@{UB}  have  been the need for an
independent  channel  for Amiga news, and the question of how to provide support
for the @{B}ICOA@{UB} @{I}User Representative @{UI}to be elected in June.

The  first  of these has been dealt with by the creation of the @{B}Amiga News Feed@{UB}.
This  is  a  system by which @{B}Amiga@{UB} news will be collected and forwarded to @{B}Amiga@{UB}
magazines,  news  sites  and  other  interested  parties. News items will not be
edited,  but  must be attributed and limited in length and format. @{B}Amiga Inc@{UB} and
others have already arranged to send out their news via the @{B}Amiga News Feed@{UB}. The
@{B}News Feed@{UB} will take the form of a read-only mailing list.

The second question is under continued discussion. The purpose of having a @{I}User 
Rep @{UI} is  to keep developers in touch with the needs of ordinary users. Therefore
we  hope  that those user group members and magazine staff in daily contact with
people  who are doing useful things with @{B}Amiga@{UB} computers, but who aren't part of
the online community, will join these discussions within the @{B}ACLG@{UB}.

@{I}FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE @{UI}

@{B}The  Amiga  Community Liaison Group@{UB} (@{B}ACLG@{UB}) made up of members of @{B}Team Amiga@{UB}, the
@{B}Jay  Miner  Society@{UB}, the @{B}User Group Network@{UB}, and the @{B}Industry Council Open Amiga@{UB}
proudly announces the formation of the @{B}Amiga News Feed@{UB}.

Our  goal  is  to provide the operation of a low noise level, timely system that
can feed news to not only the @{B}Amiga@{UB} and non-@{B}Amiga@{UB} press, but to individual users
and user groups as well.

@{I}OPERATION @{UI}

News  post  summaries, including source, email and/or URL's are sent to a single
email  address.  Spam  and  rumors  are  removed  by  a moderator, the posts are
authenticated,  and  then  pushed  thru  the  news  feed. There is NO censorship
applied.

@{I}SUBSCRIBING @{UI}

 *  Send email to @{I}majordomo@ninemoons.com @{UI}
 *  Type @{I}subscribe tamiga @{UI}in the body of the email.

The  @{B}ANF@{UB}  is  a FREE service provided to the @{B}Amiga@{UB} community with a single click
user  interface  for the posting of @{B}Amiga News@{UB}! We do ask that you visit the @{B}ANF@{UB}
webpage  and  place  the @{B}ANF@{UB} button in a prominent place on your website so that
all @{B}Amiga@{UB} users everywhere may take advantage of the service.

@{I}SPONSORS @{UI}

The  following  sponsors  are making the @{B}Amiga News Feed@{UB} avalable to you. Please
support them in their efforts.

For more information contact:
