@node woa33 "PHASE 5 AND HAAGE & PARTNER ANNOUNCE COOPERATIVE EFFORT"

@{FG Shine}PHASE 5 AND HAAGE & PARTNER ANNOUNCE COOPERATIVE EFFORT@{FG Text}

@{FG Fill}DATE: 1998/05/21@{FG Text}

May  18,  1998:  In  a joint anouncement after the recent @{B}World of Amiga@{UB} show in
London,  and  as a reaction to the plans revealed by @{B}Amiga Inc.@{UB}, @{B}Haage & Partner@{UB}
and  @{B}Phase  5  Digital Products@{UB} have emphasized their full and continued support
for  the  @{B}PowerPC@{UB}  integration.  With  joint  efforts  both vendors will further
support  the  developers  and the users of @{B}PowerPC@{UB} technology, and will ensure a
fast  growing  number of stunning and powerful applications. With many thousands
of  @{B}PowerUP@{UB} boards beeing shipped so far, a number of installed systems which is
rapidly growing, the @{B}PowerUP@{UB} boards already provide an attractive market for all
developers.  This fact is underscored by many upcoming @{B}PowerUP@{UB} releases of major
@{B}Amiga@{UB}  software  packages,  and the increasing support of software vendors which
has been agreed on during the @{B}WoA@{UB} even after the announcements of @{B}Amiga Inc.@{UB}

@{B}Haage  & Partner@{UB} and @{B}Phase 5 Digital Products@{UB} emphasized that the competition of
their  different  approaches  towards @{B}PowerPC@{UB} integration, as well as the public
dispute  about  this,  are  a matter of the past. @{I}"We will ensure that users of 
@{B}PowerUP @{UB} system  have  a transparent integration of their @{B}PowerPC @{UB}software, and 
will  see  a rich variety of most powerful applications to be released soon" @{UI}say
representatives  of  both  companies.  Further  development  of  @{B}PowerPC@{UB}  system
software  shall  be  done with close consultations between the companies; beside
that, cooperations in the development of powerful @{B}PowerPC@{UB}-based system libraries
and other OS extensions are being discussed.

In  meetings  of the managements of @{B}Haage & Partner@{UB} and @{B}Phase 5 Digital Products@{UB}
with @{B}Amiga Inc.@{UB} already during the @{B}WoA@{UB} show in London, it has been agreed that a
new  proposal  will  be  presented  to  @{B}Amiga Inc.@{UB} which outlines an alternative
option to @{B}"Amiga Bridge"@{UB} system planned by @{B}Amiga Inc.@{UB}

This  alternative  is a new @{B}PowerPC@{UB}-based system, which will feature the planned
@{B}Amiga  OS@{UB}  upgrade  and can be out for sale in the retail channels by end of the
year  already. Beyond incorporating standard industry components and interfaces,
such   a  system  can  provide  additional  options  which  allow  for  creative
development  and  expansion  in  the  spirit  of  the @{B}Amiga@{UB} and can also run the
current and next releases of @{B}AmigaOS@{UB}.

Based  on  the  @{B}PowerPC@{UB}, this system will also provide continuity and innovation
for all users and developers, and will allow the @{B}Amiga@{UB} community to take part of
such  stunning  developments  such  as  @{B}Motorola@{UB}'s  new  @{B}AltiVec@{UB}  technology, an
extension  to  the  @{B}G4  PowerPC@{UB}  processors  which  will  provide a breathtaking
performance  already  early  next year. With approval and support of @{B}Amiga Inc.@{UB},
this  technology  can  introduce  the long-awaited revival of the @{B}Amiga@{UB} platform
already  this year, quickly providing a growing market of powerful systems which
users  can  buy,  and  for  which  developers  can develop and sell software and
add-ons.

@{B}Haage & Partner@{UB} and @{B}Phase 5 Digital Products@{UB} also encourage all @{B}Amiga@{UB} developers
who  want  to  participate today in an existing innovation, and who want to be a
part  of  an  @{B}Amiga@{UB} market which provides growth, continuity and innovation from
now  on  and  during  the  next years, to speak out now and commit themselves to
support the @{B}PowerPC@{UB} as the heart of the next generation of @{B}Amiga@{UB} systems.

