@node woa34 "FIRST REPORT FROM WOA PRESS CONFERENCE"

@{FG Shine}FIRST REPORT FROM WOA PRESS CONFERENCE@{FG Text}

@{FG Fill}DATE: 1998/05/22@{FG Text}

Subject: Overview of the @{B}WOA@{UB} press conference
Date: Sat, 16 May 1998 00:18:04 +0100
From: @{I}Fabrice COLIN @{UB}(@{I}F.P.J.P.Colin@herts.ac.uk @{UI})
Organization: EUDIL 98, GTR 95
Newsgroups: comp.sys.amiga.misc

Hi there,

Here  I  am,  back  from  the  press  conference  given  by  @{B}AInc@{UB}  at Novotel in
Hammersmith.  I won't give too many details as I would like to go to bed :-) but
rather give an overview of @{B}AInc@{UB} annoucement. Well I'm quite excited ...

The  @{B}Amiga@{UB} as it is known now (@{B}OS 3.1@{UB}, @{B}AA@{UB} and @{B}68k@{UB}) is declared legacy, or @{B}"Amiga
Classic"@{UB} in @{B}AInc@{UB} terms.

An  efficient  development  platform  is  required  to  incorporate  all the new
technologies   we   have   missed  during  these  years.  It  should  bring  the
@{B}Amiga@{UB}  technologies to a wider audience as well as give a base for @{B}AOS 4.0@{UB} which
will  support memory protection, @{B}SMP@{UB}... on one hand and @{B}PCI@{UB}, @{B}AGP@{UB}, @{B}DVD@{UB} ... on the
other hand.

The  sad  thing  is that this @{B}"Amiga Bridge"@{UB} will be @{B}x86@{UB} based. No mention about
@{B}PPC@{UB},  at  least  nothing  really  clear  even when @{I}W.Dietrich, @{UI}who seemed to get
nervous,   asked   if   @{B}AInc@{UB}   intended  to  kill  the  hardware  manufacturers.
Nevertheless, this bridge is destined to be transitional only. As @{B}AInc@{UB} will stay
a  software  development  firm only, other designs will be welcomed. As far as I
have  understood,  it  should not be a big problem since @{B}"Amiga Classic"@{UB} will be
supported  through the @{B}Siamese@{UB} system. The thing is: will @{B}AInc@{UB} back up those who
want to do a @{B}PPC@{UB} port ? It seems so!

@{B}AOS 4.0@{UB}, due for Nov 98 (yes) will be developed on top of a 3rd party kernel. We
don't know anything yet, apart from the fact that @{B}AInc@{UB} is currently in dicussion
with several other firms such as @{B}Be@{UB} ...

@{B}AOS  5.0@{UB}  (end  of 99), aimed at the @{B}"Digital Convergence"@{UB} platform (still to be
defined/unveiled)  will  be  aimed  at customers, although @{B}AOS 4.0@{UB} would also be
usable for an end user. @{B}3.5@{UB} is cancelled so the average user will wait 18 months
for a revision of the OS. @{B}"Classic"@{UB} and @{B}"Bridge"@{UB} compatibilities will be assured
via emulation.

@{I}Jim Collas, @{UI}Senior Vice President of @{B}Gateway@{UB}, who has been put under pressure by
3  MIB  (who are they ? I don't know) and a bloke from @{B}Alive Mediasoft@{UB}, promised
to  clarify  the  situation  regarding the @{B}PPC@{UB} tomorrow. That's it. More to come
tomorrow I hope ....

PS: This post has been written in the train while I should have been sleeping. I
must also say that I have eaten too much at the buffet 8>) --

