@node woa39 "FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS ABOUT ANNOUNCEMENT AT WORLD OF AMIGA"

@{FG Shine}FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS ABOUT ANNOUNCEMENT AT WORLD OF AMIGA@{FG Text}

@{FG Fill}DATE: 1998/05/31@{FG Text}

This news release is from the @{B}Amiga Inc.@{UB} site at @{B}http://www.amiga.com/@{UB}

@{I}FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE @{UI}

 * @{I}Are you abandoning the @{B}Amiga @{UB}? @{UI}

No,  we  are  focusing  our  efforts  on  the development of the next generation
architecture  and  operating system. We are working with third parties to create
an open architecture necessary to bring the @{B}Amiga@{UB} back for the future.

 * @{I}Isn't the new @{B}Amiga @{UB}really just a @{B}PC @{UB}with @{B}Amiga @{UB}slapped into it? @{UI}

While it is true that the next generation of @{B}Amiga@{UB} will use the @{B}x.86@{UB} platform as
a  development system, this is meant to be used as a bridge to take the @{B}Amiga@{UB} to
version  5.0.  @{B}Amiga  5.0@{UB}  is a brand new @{B}Amiga@{UB}, using the most evolutionary and
revolutionary technology of software and hardware architectures.

 * @{I}Why didn't you choose @{B}PowerPC @{UB}for the next generation @{B}Amiga @{UB}platform? @{UI}

The  @{B}Motorola@{UB}  roadmap  does  not  match  our vision for the future that we have
targeted  for  the @{B}Amiga@{UB}. The @{B}Amiga Classic@{UB} line will continue to support @{B}PPC@{UB} as
an accelerator the current systems.

 * @{I}So do I just throw away all of my @{B}Amiga @{UB}applications and start over? @{UI}

No.  The  @{B}Amiga  4.0@{UB}  will  support  most  of your existing applications through
software  emulation.  We are working with another third party hardware vendor to
develop  a hardware add-on (@{B}Amiga Classic Card@{UB}) that will make the bridge system
backwards compatible.

 * @{I}Are you really abandoning the @{B}Amiga OS @{UB}and licensing another OS? @{UI}

We  are  NOT  abandoning  the  @{B}Amiga  OS@{UB}.  We  are  investigating  the option of
leveraging  a  state  of  the  art kernel of another OS to speed the development
process and decrease our time to market the next generations of the @{B}Amiga OS@{UB}.

 * @{I}Summary @{UI}

We  are  focusing  our energy on bringing the @{B}Amiga@{UB} technology and the community
into  the  21st  century,  ahead  of the pack. We will target our efforts on the
operating  system and an open architecture necessary to truly be a leader in the
multimedia, digital convergence marketplace.

MEDIA CONTACT:
@{I}Bill McEwen @{UI}
@{B}Amiga Incorporated@{UB}
@{I}billm@amigainc.com @{UI}
