@node not39 "DEIMOS DESIGN FINALISES FUTURE PLANS"

@{FG Shine}DEIMOS DESIGN FINALISES FUTURE PLANS{FG Text}

@{FG Fill}DATE: 1998/05/29@{FG Text}

After  completing  our  analysis  of the current @{B}Amiga@{UB} market, Deimos Design has
finalised  it's  future  plans. Since early 1997, @{B}Deimos Design@{UB} has existed with
one  goal  in  mind,  to  support  the  @{B}Amiga@{UB}  with high specification games. In
addition  to  this,  we hoped for a modest return to cover our investment (time,
money and effort) in @{B}Maim & Mangle@{UB}.

Since  then,  many  things (both good and bad) have happened. Unfortunately, one
overwhelming  factor  has remained - the buying user base has constantly eroded.
While  @{B}Amiga  Incorporated@{UB} have recently announced their plans for the future, a
new  influx  of  users  cannot  realistically  be expected for at least eighteen
months.

The  projected returns from the current market (even hopelessly optimistic ones)
do not justify the amount of work we have already invested in @{B}M&M@{UB} (on top of the
work  that  remains).  We  do  not see this situation as changing until the next
generation  of  machine  is  released.  By that time, @{B}Maim & Mangle@{UB} will be "old
hat", many other similar games will have been released.

As  a  result, @{B}Deimos Design@{UB} has made the rather painful decision to concentrate
on  the @{B}PC@{UB} CD-ROM format, with the aid and support of @{B}Vulcan SW Limited@{UB}. This is
an  interim  decision, and one which can be reevaluated when the @{B}Amiga@{UB} market is
once again viable. For the immediate future however, we can no longer ignore the
economic realities.

As  a  sign of good faith to the many users whom have shown us their support, we
have  arranged  a  special  deal  with  @{B}The World Foundry@{UB}. We have disclosed all
information  pertaining  to  the  @{B}Amiga@{UB} version of @{B}Maim and Mangle@{UB} (source code,
design specs, and other materials) to @{B}The World Foundry@{UB} free of charge. They are
free to do with the project as they please, be that to work upon and release the
game in full, or use parts of it in their upcoming projects.

If  you  would  like to offer them your support for releasing @{B}Maim & Mangle@{UB}, @{B}The
World Foundry@{UB} can be contacted at:

		@{B}http://www.worldfoundry.home.ml.org@{UB}

For more information concerning this announcement, please contact:

		@{I}deimos@fundy.net @{UI}

