@node not41 "AMIGA INC. TRANSCRIPT INTERNATIONAL AMIGA' 98 TORONTO"

@{FG Shine}AMIGA INC. TRANSCRIPT INTERNATIONAL AMIGA' 98 TORONTO@{FG Text}

@{FG Fill}DATE: 1998/05/31@{FG Text}

@{I}FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE @{UI}

@{I}No One can walk backwards into the Future. @{UI}

The  strategy  is clear, we can combine computer worlds with this concept and my
credo is, we will have a bright future... @{I}"Keep the momentum going"! @{UI}

Dear Ladies and Gentlemen, Distinguished Guests.

I'm very pleased to join the @{B}International Amiga '98@{UB} here in Toronto again. Last
time that I visited Toronto was in 1995, three years ago already.

Let  me  give  you  a  short overview of what happened in London at the @{B}World of
Amiga@{UB}  two weeks ago. My collegues from our Research and Development department,
@{B}Amiga  Inc.@{UB}  have  announced  the  long  expected statement. In the morning, the
announcement  was  held  to  the  @{B}Amiga@{UB}  press  only  and  in the evening it was
disclosed to the broad public. It was even broadcast via the Internet.

Of  course  there  are a lot of different opinions, but my point of view is that
every  step  forward  is  a  positive step and a step into the future. How do we
explain our @{B}Amiga@{UB} fanatics that we are focusing our effort on the development of
the next generation to use the @{B}x86@{UB} platform? At that point, I want to thank @{I}Jeff
Schindler @{UI} who has done a great job in a very difficult situation.

Please  be sure we have a target for @{B}Amiga@{UB}. The @{B}Amiga classic@{UB} line will continue
to  support @{B}PPC@{UB} as an accellerator for the current systems supported by @{B}Phase 5@{UB},
@{B}Haage  & Partner@{UB}, and many more licensees. The @{B}Amiga OS 4.0@{UB} will support most of
your  existing  applications  through  software  emulation.  We are working with
another  third-party hardware vendor to develop a hardware add-on (@{B}Amiga classic@{UB}
card) that will make the bridge system backwards compatible.

While it is true that the next generation of @{B}Amiga@{UB} will use the @{B}x.86@{UB} platform as
a  development system, this is meant to be used as a bridge to take the @{B}Amiga@{UB} to
version  5.0.  @{B}Amiga  5.0@{UB}  is a brand-new @{B}Amiga@{UB}, using the most evolutionary and
revolutionary technology of software and hardware architectures. Later on, @{I}Jeff @{UI}
and his staff will go into further details.

Let's go back to sales and marketing.

The  new  @{B}Amigas@{UB},  as  well  as  the @{B}Amiga Classic@{UB}, will be distributed by @{B}Amiga
International,  Inc.@{UB}  the  sales  and  marketing  division. I don't want to miss
mentioning our new CD @{B}"Theme of Amiga"@{UB} performed by Annex at the @{B}World of Amiga@{UB}.
The  two  performances per day were such a success that the CD player broke down
during  the  dance act, because of the energetic performance of our dance group.
If  you  like the new song, you can buy the CD for 15 Canadian dollars here with
me. With the money that @{B}Amiga International@{UB} earns by selling the CD's, I plan to
establish  a fund to support the @{B}Amiga@{UB} Community. Until now, the fund amounts to
500 USD. Please watch our website @{B}www.amiga.de@{UB} as we've prepared a small musical
extraction for you.

What  else...  We  are  already  preparing our next @{B}Amiga@{UB} fair @{B}Computer '98@{UB} in
Cologne,  Germany.  I  started a new advertisement in the magazine @{B}Amazing Amiga@{UB}
and  @{B}Newtekniques@{UB}.  I  hope  as  much as possible of you will come to Cologne to
support  me  and  to see the news of our Research and Development company, @{B}Amiga
Inc.@{UB}  Of  course, our dance group @{B}Annex@{UB} will perform our new @{B}Amiga@{UB} theme. As you
may  know  in Cologne there exists (except the fair) the famous Kolsch beer, and
also very delicious German sausages which are available at our booth and free of
charge.

In  addition,  we plan to set up a stage to present the dance performance @{B}"Theme
of  Amiga"@{UB}  of @{B}Annex@{UB}, to hold meetings, speeches and presentations. This year we
expect between 35,000 and 45,000 visitors from November 13th to 15th. And I hope
I will meet many of you there too. I think it is worth coming.

@{B}Amiga@{UB} is back... Back for the future...

I'm  conviced that the drivers - our community - are already all set for another
exciting  race  with  @{B}Amiga@{UB}  for which @{I}Jeff @{UI}will develop suitable cars - our new
@{B}Amiga@{UB}  generation  - and I will broaden the road to go this street together with
you.

Thank you and enjoy the fair.

