@node art2 "ELASTIC DREAMS"

@{FG Shine}ELASTIC DREAMS@{FG Text}

Many  people who have just bought their @{B}PowerPC@{UB} boards and thinking if they have
done the right thing, Now have a excuse to see their processors screamming!.

I  only  can  say  that @{B}Elastic Dreams@{UB} is the most revolutionary graphic retouch
program  on the @{B}Amiga@{UB}, the requester and menu age is over, everything here is as
intuitive as possible.

I  would  to tell that @{B}ED@{UB} is the only program in the market that do that, but on
other  platforms  exists  a  program  more  or  less  as  @{B}ED@{UB},  which  is  highly
"inspirated"  on the famous @{B}Kai's Power Goo@{UB} so if you know that program, you can
imaginate the power of @{B}ED@{UB}.

Before  starting,  I  have  to  say  that  @{B}ED@{UB}  is  a  graphic retouch, morphing,
composition, and animation program in real-time, that mean we don't have to wait
to  see  the desired effect, every deformation that we make in the image will be
shown instanstly, well, in fact, its depends on processor, but on a @{B}040@{UB} at 40mhz
or less you can get more that satisfactory effects, been incredible on a @{B}060/PPC@{UB}
equiped @{B}Amiga@{UB}.

@{B}Elastic  Dreams@{UB}  consists  of  three programs: @{B}Composer@{UB}, @{B}Manager@{UB} and the @{B}Elastic
Part@{UB}, the editor itself.

@{B}Composer@{UB} is where we can "join" images together and see its combination.

The  @{B}Elastic Part@{UB}: Where you can realize the full power of @{B}ED@{UB}, you can apply any
operator to deform, blend, strech, or add Especial Effects.

It's also possible to create animations with ease and see how the images deform,
Everything is made in real time!

The third part is named @{B}Manager@{UB} where the whole program is configurated, you can
select the background of the program and the level of quality, anti-alias, etc.

@{B}ED@{UB} supports some third-party programs, it can scan pictures using @{B}Scaquix@{UB} and it
prints using @{B}Turbo Print@{UB}.

When  doing  animation, frames can be saved one by one to proccess them later or
you can make animations in @{B}IFF@{UB} format or use the custom @{B}ED@{UB}-anim format.

In  every moment, the program works in 24bits, that's 16 millions of colors!, so
the  quality  is  ensured,  and  of  course  the program can also be used on @{B}AGA@{UB}
machines with incredible results.

@{B}Elastic Dreams@{UB} has a huge graphic format support:

@{B}
Load: Acbm, Alias, Bmp, Datatypes, Fits, Gif, Iff, Iff24, Impulse, Ipbm, Jpeg,
      MacPaint, Pbm, Pcx, Pgm, PhotoCD, Png, Ppm, Psd, Qrt, Raw RGB, Rendition,
      Rle, Scanquix, Sgi, Sunraster, Svg, Targa, Tiff, Tim!!, WaveFront, Yuvn

Save: Alias, Iff, Iff Deep, Impulse, Jpeg, Pbm, Pgm, Ppm, Qrt, Rendition, Yuvn
@{UB}

Also  the  authors promise any module needed for other graphic format, always if
you are a registered user.

We can found some effects like Waves, Ripples, whirls, Emboss, Strech and more!.

@{B}Requeriments
------------@{UB}

   @{B}Minimum
   -------@{UB}

   - @{B}Amiga@{UB} with @{B}68030@{UB}
   - @{B}WB 3.0@{UB}
   - @{B}AGA@{UB} or Graphics Card
   - 8 mgs Ram
   - 20 mgs HD
   - CD-ROM

   @{B}Recommended
   -----------@{UB}

   - @{B}Amiga@{UB} with @{B}68060@{UB} or @{B}PowerPC@{UB} processor
   - Graphics Card
   - 32 mgs Ram

Due to the big size of 24bits images, the more the memory, the better result you
will get.

@{B}Install
-------@{UB}

As  the  program  is  distributed  in  CD,  you only have to execute the install
program,  which is based on the Commodore Standard Installer and everything will
be ready to atart.

